quran[63]{c,v,t}:
  76,19,"Youthful lads, staying young forever, would (go around and) wait on them. (So handsome), you would take them for scattered pearls when you see them"
  76,20,"In the paradise, you will find (the idyllic bliss and) blessings everywhere; splendors of the great empire"
  76,21,They will wear green garments made of fine silk and rich brocade. They shall don silver (arm bands and) bracelets as adornments. Their Lord will give them a pure (refreshing) drink
  76,22,"(They shall hear), \"This is really your reward. Your efforts (in life) have found acceptance (and borne fruit in the afterlife)"
  76,23,"Indeed, it is We Who revealed to you the Qur´an in stages, a little at a time"
  76,24,"Therefore, submit to the commands of your Lord, patiently. And do not obey the sinners, the unbelievers among them"
  76,25,"And remember your Lord´s name, each morning and evening"
  76,26,Prostrate before Him during part of the night. Chant His praises during the long hours of the night
  76,27,"In fact, the unbelievers love the present (transient) life, the one easy to earn (and attain), while they put behind (and out of their mind), the remembrance of a grievous onerous day"
  76,28,"It is We Who created them. We gave them their strength and vigor. Whenever We wish, We can replace them all together. We can easily bring in their place others like them"
  76,29,"Indeed, this (Qur´an) is a reminder! (Now), whoever wishes may follow the path (that leads) to his Lord"
  76,30,"But you cannot will anything, unless Allah wills it so. Indeed, Allah is all-Knowing, all-Wise"
  76,31,"He ushers into His mercy whomever He wills. For the evil doers, He has prepared a painful punishment"
  77,1,"(I swear by the wind) that is sent in waves, and buffets gently"
  77,2,And the violent wind that raises storms
  77,3,"Then, scatters things around"
  77,4,And splits them asunder
  77,5,And instills (in man) the remembrance (of Allah)
  77,6,"As a plea, and as a warning"
  77,7,"What you are being promised, (the Day of Decision), will very surely occur"
  77,8,(It will occur) when the stars lose their luster
  77,9,The sky bursts asunder
  77,10,The mountains (blow up and) crumble
  77,11,And when all the messengers are summoned (to bear witness)
  77,12,Until what day has it been put off
  77,13,Till the Day of Decision
  77,14,And what do you suppose is the Day of Decision
  77,15,Misery that day is for those who (dispute and) deny (the truth)
  77,16,Did We not wipe out the unbelievers of earlier times
  77,17,We will make (the unbelievers of) the later generations follow (the same fate as that of) the earlier ones
  77,18,This is what We do to the criminals
  77,19,Misery that day is for those who (dispute and) deny (the truth)
  77,20,Did We not create you from a (tiny) drop of filthy fluid
  77,21,Which We lodged in a secure and stable setting
  77,22,For a known period
  77,23,This is what We destined! How very excellent is Our destiny
  77,24,Misery that day is for those who (dispute and) deny (the truth)
  77,25,Did We not appoint the earth to accommodate
  77,26,"The living, and the dead"
  77,27,"And on the earth, We placed the high mountains; and We gave you sweet water to drink"
  77,28,Misery that day is for those who (dispute and) deny (the truth)
  77,29,"(They would be told), \"Proceed now and enter (hell), the very thing you used to deny (so vehemently)"
  77,30,Proceed under the three-pronged shadow
  77,31,"It neither provides the cool shade, nor lends protection against the (fierce) flames"
  77,32,"Indeed, it will hurl sparks as tall as a (lofty) palace"
  77,33,Which would look like yellow camels
  77,34,Misery that day is for those who (dispute and) deny (the truth)
  77,35,Nothing will they say that day
  77,36,Nor would they be allowed to offer excuses (and explanations)
  77,37,Misery that day is for those who (dispute and) deny (the truth)
  77,38,"This is the Day of Decision. (Today) We have assembled all of you together, along with (all) the earlier generations"
  77,39,"If you have a trick left (up your sleeves), play it now! Outwit Me"
  77,40,Misery that day is for those who (dispute and) deny (the truth)
  77,41,"The pious ones (that day) would be amidst cool shades, fountains"
  77,42,And fruits of their choice
  77,43,"Eat and drink, and relish your rewards! (It is yours) in return for what you used to do"
  77,44,This is really how We reward the righteous
  77,45,Misery that day is for those who (dispute and) deny (the truth)
  77,46,"(Oh unbelievers)! Eat and enjoy (your possessions) just a little while longer. Indeed, you are the criminals"
  77,47,Misery that day is for those who (dispute and) deny (the truth)
  77,48,"When asked to kneel (before their Lord), they refused"
  77,49,Misery that day is for those who (dispute and) deny (the truth)
  77,50,"So, after this (Qur´an), is there any other discourse they can (accept and) believe"